News24 Correspondent Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Thohoyandou - Police were searching on Monday for a suspect who killed a 24-year-old and left his body alongside a road in Shayandima location, outside Thohoyandou, Limpopo, on Christmas Day. "It is alleged that the deceased was at his home at night when he received a call; he then went out and was later found dead," &nbsp;Lieutenant Colonel Moatshe Ngope said in a statement. "His cellphone was taken away during this incident." The motive for the crime was still not known, Ngope said.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.